{
  "texts": [
    "DeBERTa enhances the BERT and RoBERTa 37 models through two innovative techniques.",
    "The first is the disentangled attention mechanism, where each word is represented by two separate vectors-one for its content and the other for its position.",
    "The second technique involves an improved mask decoder, which replaces the standard softmax output layer for predicting masked tokens during model pretraining.",
    "These advancements result in outstanding performance across a range of benchmarks.",
    "Performance evaluation for the NER, KSR and RE downstream tasks on TFDR corpus utilized three metrics: micro-F1, macro-F1, and weighted-F1."
  ]
}